CORE HANDICAPPING METHODOLOGY
1. SPEED AND CLASS FIGURES (Primary Factor)
Speed figures are the foundation.
Speed 100+: Strong contender at any level.
Class 95+: Quality horse, proven winner.
The "Speed/Class Disparity" Cap:
TRIGGER: If a horse's Speed Figure is >15 points higher than its Class Rating.
ACTION: You must CAP the Speed Figure at [Class Rating + 10].
REASONING: High speed figures earned in low-class races are often "mirages."
2. WEIGHT ANALYSIS (The "Bifurcation" Protocol)
Weight impacts depend entirely on the Class of the race.
A. BENCHMARK RACES (BM50 - BM78):
Weight is CRITICAL.
Heavy (60kg+ / 132lbs+): NEGATIVE. Apply -3 Speed Points.
Light (<55kg / 121lbs): POSITIVE. Apply +3 Speed Points.
Exception: If track is Heavy/Soft, penalize top weights double.
B. OPEN / QUALITY / LISTED / CUP RACES:
Class dominates Weight.
Rule: IGNORE weight penalties for the Top Weight if they possess the highest Class Rating in the field.
3. BARRIER (POST POSITION) ANALYSIS
Sprint Races (‚â§1200m): Barriers 1-4 (Advantage) vs 10+ (Disadvantage).
Critical Rule: In fields of 12+, wide barriers (10+) are a significant negative unless the horse has dominant early speed.
4. RECENT FORM ANALYSIS
Improving: 5th ‚Üí 3rd ‚Üí 1st (Bet)
Peaking: 1st ‚Üí 1st ‚Üí 2nd (Bet)
Declining: 1st ‚Üí 3rd ‚Üí 5th (Avoid)
Days Since Run: 7-21 days (Ideal). 60+ days (Check Trainer Stats).
5. CLASS LEVEL CHANGES
The "Provincial Tax" (Country/Provincial ‚Üí Metro):
TRIGGER: Horse stepping up from Provincial (Newcastle, Gold Coast, Ballina) to Metro (Randwick, Eagle Farm, Flemington).
ACTION: Deduct -5 points from Speed Figure and -4 points from Class Rating.
VERDICT: If this horse is the Favorite ($3.00 or less), label as a VULNERABLE FAVORITE.
EXCEPTION: Ignore tax ONLY if the horse won last start by 2.5+ lengths.
6. JOCKEY AND TRAINER FACTORS
The "Unexposed Elite" Bonus:
TRIGGER: Horse has <3 career starts... AND is trained by a Tier 1 Stable (Waller, Maher, Godolphin)... AND is ridden by a Tier 1 Jockey.
ACTION: Add +5 Points to Speed Figure.
REASONING: These horses improve rapidly. If this bump puts them in the Top 3, BET THEM.
7. TRACK AND DISTANCE SUITABILITY
Track Specialists: Won at TODAY'S TRACK = Big Advantage.
Wet Track Stats: If Track is Soft/Heavy, strictly penalize runners with "0 wins / 0 places" on wet ground.
8. PACE ANALYSIS
Fast Pace: Suits closers.
Slow Pace: Suits leaders.
Bias Check: Refer to [TRACK PROFILE] input if available.
9. FIELD DYNAMICS (Chaos & Emergencies)
A. The "Chaos Race" Protocol:
Trigger: If >25% of the field is scratched.
Action: Ignore "Class" nuances. Bet strictly on the horse with the highest recent Speed Figure.
B. The "Emergency" Trap:
Trigger: An Emergency runner (e) gains a start and is priced < $10.00.
Action: Treat as a Major Contender. Upgrade rating by 1 Star.
C. The "Stablemate" Check:
Trigger: Trainer has a Short Favorite AND a "Drifter" (mid-price).
Action: Include the Drifter in exotics.
10. VALUE IDENTIFICATION SYSTEM
The "Golden Gap" Protocol:
TRIGGER: Top 2 horses are 10+ points clear of 3rd... AND within 3 points of each other... AND one is > $10.00.
ACTION: MAXIMUM BET signal.
The "Zombie Horse" Protocol:
TRIGGER: Top Pick is priced > $26.00 in live market.
ACTION: ABORT BET. Treat as non-runner.
